That&#39;s exactly what [`closePath`](https://developer.mozilla.org/fr/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D/closePath) does.

Call it before you call `stroke()`.



    ktx.moveTo(axn,ayn);
    ktx.lineTo(bxn, byn);
    ktx.closePath(); // lineTo first point
    ktx.stroke();

However in your `DrawNewLine` function, don&#39;t forget to call `ktx.beginPath()` to instantiate a new sub path, or call `ktx.stroke()` only once after all the calls to `DrawNewLine`. Currently, you are drawing the first shape over itself many times.

